Trump O'Meter is a project which represents a chrome extension which classifies a piece of text on how likely it is to be a Trump's thought. 
It s: 

Python ANN (Artificial Neural Net) build from scratch;
Twitter API to fetch previous Trump's posts;
HTML/CSS for the chrome extension;
Youtube to mp3 converter to fetch Trump's voice;
Twilio API to send and receive messages;

Authors: Simeon Kostadinov (University of Birmingham), Yusof Bandar and Pritam Sangani (Manchester Metropolitan University).

Project - Water Disease Protection system
Many African countries suffer from poor water supply and drainage, which in turn leads to flash floods and droughts. Both flash floods and droughts in affected areas are very likely to ca disease outbreaks, added to the original problem of lack or surplus of water. Therefore, by  rainfall predictions it is possible to predict the likelihood of disease, droughts, water shortage problems and floods. Predicting the possibility of these hazards then allows emergency response teams to  informed decisions on where to best deploy emergency resources. 
The protection system s the following data elements:
·         Spatial Population coverage/villages
·         Medical centres
·         Cholera cases (per region)
·         Rainfall prediction
·         Drought index (SPI)
·         Poverty
·         Livestock
·         Accessibility to water
